AddNotesComponent.bdNotes:
Urgent and Emergent Services coverage outside of the United States and its territories has an annual $250.00 deductible, then 20% coinsurance until lifetime maximum benefit of $50,000. 

Medical Associates Health Plans covers Medicare eligible emergency transportation via ambulance. However, emergency transportation received outside the United States and its territories does not include transportation expenses to return a beneficiary to the United States (i.e. airfare).
